[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837759026654&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837759026654&q=raw">body</a>]</b>


    Having spent considerable time testing domain software recently I've
come to feel the need for a documented domain test suite and test database.

    Unless someone has done this already, I'm planning to create a sub-domain
of cs.net  (e.g. test.cs.net) which contains various interesting test cases
(such as CNAME RRs which point across domains, a list of MX RRs which will
cause the truncation bit to be set, at least one example of every RR, 
wildcard names, etc.).  Has anyone tried to do this already?  Does anyone
have suggested cases for the test suite?

    I'll document the test suite and post to name-droppers if there is enough
interest.

Craig Partridge
CSNET Technical Staff

craig@csnet-sh or craig@sh.cs.net (CSNET)
craig@loki.bbn.com (ARPA)

